  "summary": "Memory exhaustion in query parameter parsing in net/url",
  "details": "The net/url package does not set a limit on the number of query parameters in a query.\n\nWhile the maximum size of query parameters in URLs is generally limited by the maximum request header size, the net/http.Request.ParseForm method can parse large URL-encoded forms. Parsing a large form containing many unique query parameters can cause excessive memory consumption.",
